This paper presents a novel algorithm for autonomous vehicle navigation that involves optimization-based maneuver planning, collision avoidance, and trajectory computation. These topics are closely related to robotics (cs.RO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a data-driven approach, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely candidates for this paper.
